
            Title: The State of AI in Operations 2025
            Summary: In January 2025, a survey of over 1,000 managers and senior business leaders assessed AI adoption in operations. The findings indicate that 28% of businesses are already using AI, with 45% having active implementation plans. Key insights include investment trends, challenges in AI adoption, and the role of AI agents. Businesses are planning to increase their AI investments significantly, with many intending to spend over $100,000. The survey highlights a positive outlook for AI adoption across various industries, with 73% of businesses either using AI or planning to implement it.
